      "content": "Skipping a basal insulin dose without medical guidance creates a dangerous uncertainty because your body cannot predict how your sugar levels will rise after a normal morning of eating and your nighttime glucose baseline. While a severe hypoglycemia leading to a medical emergency is a frightening possibility, untreated hyperglycemia poses its own severe risks like diabetic ketoacidosis or long-term organ damage, making the decision far too risky to guess on your own this late. The safest immediate course of action is to check your blood sugar and take only a fraction of your usual dose if you absolutely must sleep, rather than skipping the medication entirely to avoid potential highs.",
